RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (QUARTER HORSE RACE 2 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 81. Claiming Purse 14500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since September 5 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DEBT MONGER chased 3wide on the backstretch, continued three wide on the turn, dueled in upper stretch with rival and floated rival to the rail to prove best late. KING ADROCK away well, led in between rivals on the backstretch, continued to lead on the turn, entered lane in the two path, floated in by outside rival and outgamed late while in tight along the rail. WHOA BUDDY stalked pace two wide on the backstretch, continued off rail on the turn, launched bid along the rail and grinded up for third. AROUND THE DIAL stalked pace three wide on the backstretch, continued three wide on the turn, asked and delivered a mild rally in the lane to improve. ABADON pressed paced in between on the backstretch, got to rail entering the turn, unable to keep up with pair of outside rivals entering the stretch, so eased out around them and came up empty when roused. RIVER TIBER pressed pace along the rail on the backstretch, pinched back entering the turn, and failed to threaten thereafter. DIVINELY DIVERSE in tight and pinched back, causing him to clip heels, fell back and not asked in the backstretch, advanced well under own power on the turn, but failed to improve in the lane. FAMOUS ROCK STAR settled along the inside on the backstretch, had to take up abruptly when RIVER TIBER was pinched and stopped in front of him, took till mid turn to regather and coasted to wire while in the three path. PLEASE NOTE, RACE WAS HAND TIMED

ENTRY.NAME: Abadon
ENTRY.COMMENT: pressed inside, eased out 3wide, weakened upper stretch

RACE.RACE_TEXT: Los Alamitos Super Derby - Grade1 LOS ALAMITOS (QUARTER HORSE RACE 10 400 Y Dirt CR: 97. Derby Purse 935650. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS. Weight 126lbs. (No sex allowance). Horses which qualified to this race must pass the entry box in the usual manner. THE WINNER RECEIVES A PRESUMPTIVE INVITATION TO THE 2023 CHAMPION OF CHAMPIONS. A trophy will be presented to the own er of the winner.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: JERIKO off bit slow, but kept his path, leveled approaching the gap, asked once midway and finished strong under a drive to get up. SICARIO V off a bit slow with rider hitting assistant starter, accelerated strongly to take the lead by the gap, kept to task and nailed by hard charging rival at the wire. PARTY POLITICS continued his gate antics, away well, asked right handed and drifted in a path early, kept under steady right handed urging and outclosed by the winner. FEARLESS MOON away well enough, asked right handed early, kept under a strong drive throughout and caught late for third in a game effort. GHOST WITHA FIRE away well, asked right handed early, kept to task while unable to match strides with the top finishers. HES CHICKLESS away best, asked early, kept to task, began to get leg weary reaching the final half and weakened under a drive. NAVAJA got away with the leaders, under a hand drive early, asked midway and failed to respond. FUTURE VERSION ducked out five paths at the start, continued to lean out the first fifty yards, shifted in passing the eighth pole, finally leveled out in the final sixteenth to finish with something left in the tank. HES JUDGEANDJURY came away a bit slow, lacked needed quickness to hold lane, rider sensed he was about to lose his path approaching the final eighth and preemptively altered three to four paths out, and failed to have any finish.

ENTRY.NAME: Hes Judgeandjury
ENTRY.OWNER: Jones, Jeff D. and Holt, Steve A.
ENTRY.COMMENT: off bit slow, altered out 1/8, no bid

ENTRY.NAME: Future Version
ENTRY.OWNER: Rojas Racing LLC and Moya Juan H
